
Implement clearDomCache method in the Router

Factor out the Dom cache clearing from clearPreviousHistory(), and export it as a Router method.

This facilitates a use case like chaning language preference, where you can refreshPage() to reload the current page in the current language, and then call clearDomCache() to ensure that pages in the history will be reloaded in the current language if they are revisited.

Fix parameter typing for Router.navigate

Declare `side` argument optional in panel.[open|close]

The types currently force you to provide a `side` argument for `panel.open`/`panel.close`. This relaxes the types to make that optional.

Merge pull request #654 from Tarekajaj/master

Scan Dates Range, array accept mixed types (single date + date range)

Add support for DOM content in router.preprocess

I wish to use Angular + Framework7 together. For that i should compile pages content with angular.$compile.
I use router.preprocess to achive this. But $compile returns DOM element with angular scope, so i can`t
return HTML text from preprocess function. In this PR router is modifed with additional check. If
content is not string then router appends content and don`t use innerHTML field.

Example of my preprocess function:
```coffeescript
    @framework7 = new Framework7
      swipePanel: 'left'
      preprocess: (content, url, next) =>
        compiled = @compile content
        compiledContent = compiled @scope
        compiledContent
```
